e Team USA for the Paris Olympics byfinishing third in the women's shot put.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\", \"score\": 0.9999997166596988, \"rank\": 1.9362318328914368e-07, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\"}, {\"begin\": 1195, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4423076397704626e-19, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chase Jackson won the event and Raven Saunders took second to round out the Olympic women's shot put team for the U.S.  Also winning finals on Saturday were Andrew Evans (men's discus), Tara Davis-Woodhall (women's long jump) and Weini Kelati (women's 10,000 meters).\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\", \"score\": 0.9985589768076754, \"rank\": 0.0014402891357767618, \"text\": \"Chase\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 0.9999999130413963, \"rank\": 8.689530480258304e-08, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raven_Saunders\", \"score\": 1.0, 